---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const ptBody = `

  <header class="hero hero--with-image">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <div class="hero-eyebrow eyebrow">Dental &amp; Wellness Professionals &middot; Physical Therapists (DPTs)</div>
          <h1 class="display-1">Mortgages for Florida physical therapists (DPTs) &mdash; hospital-employed PTs, outpatient clinic chain PTs, private practice owners, home health / SNF PRN PTs, and sports / subspecialty PTs &mdash; qualifying on W-2 base + productivity bonuses + S-corp K-1 + 1099 PRN with multi-source synthesis.</h1>
          <p class="lead hero-subtitle">Florida physical therapists operate as Doctors of Physical Therapy (DPTs) with entry-level doctorate required since 2016 (pre-2016 MPT clinicians grandfathered), completing 3-year <a href="https://www.capteonline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">CAPTE-accredited</a> doctoral program followed by <a href="https://www.fsbpt.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">FSBPT</a> NPTE (National Physical Therapy Examination) for licensure, with <a href="https://www.apta.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">APTA (American Physical Therapy Association)</a> professional society membership + Florida Board of Physical Therapy Practice licensure, and optional <a href="https://www.apta.org/your-career/abpts" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">ABPTS (American Board of Physical Therapy Specialties)</a> board certification in clinical specialty (OCS Orthopedic, SCS Sports, NCS Neurologic, GCS Geriatric, PCS Pediatric, CCS Cardiovascular). <strong>Florida physical therapist practice spans five primary categories: hospital-employed PT with W-2 base $75K-$95K + productivity bonuses + benefits + sometimes shift differentials; outpatient clinic chain PT at large chain (Select Medical + Athletico + US Physical Therapy + Ivy Rehab + ATI Physical Therapy + others) with W-2 base $70K-$95K + productivity bonus + sometimes shift differential, total $80K-$115K; private practice PT owner operating S-corp election PLLC with W-2 wages + K-1 distribution + sometimes multi-clinic ownership + sometimes athletic team consulting + sometimes practice building real estate, senior practice owners $150K-$400K+ income; home health / SNF (Skilled Nursing Facility) PT working PRN per-diem 1099 or W-2 with higher hourly rates ($55-$95/hour typical), substantial scheduling flexibility, total $85K-$130K+ depending on hours + setting mix; sports medicine + pediatric + specialized PT with subspecialty fellowship + ABPTS board certification + sometimes athletic team consulting (high school + collegiate + professional) + sometimes private practice + sometimes pediatric clinic, $90K-$180K+ income range.</strong> For mortgage qualifying, multi-source PT income synthesizes under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-01/general-income-information" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01</a> for W-2 + productivity with 24-month averaging, <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.2-01/underwriting-factors-and-documentation-for-a-self-employed-borrower" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">B3-3.2-01</a> for 1099 PRN home health + athletic consulting, and <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">B3-3.4-02</a> for practice owner S-corp K-1 + multi-clinic ownership with Form 1084 analysis. Professional / healthcare loan Non-QM programs with relaxed DTI + IBR/IDR student loan treatment available. <strong>Stairway Mortgage routinely handles Florida physical therapist mortgages with multi-source synthesis + practice owner K-1 + PRN 1099 + IBR/IDR + Florida healthcare industry context.</strong></p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Schedule a call with Jim</a>
            <a href="#pt-roles" class="btn btn-secondary btn-large">See PT practice roles</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-trust">
            <span class="trust-dot"></span><span>Broker NMLS #1072866</span><span>&middot;</span>
            <span>FL mortgage broker specializing in DPT multi-source: W-2 + productivity + S-corp K-1 + PRN 1099 + IBR/IDR + ABPTS board cert + APTA</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="hero-image"><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7659564/pexels-photo-7659564.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1200" alt="Florida physical therapist DPT clinical rehabilitation practice" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/1200x1500/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=DPT';"></figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="stats stats--with-image">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="stats-bar-grid">
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">$75K-$400K+ income</div><div class="stat-label">DPT income $75K (hospital-employed entry) to $400K+ (senior multi-clinic private practice owner). Multi-source spans W-2 base + productivity + S-corp K-1 + PRN 1099 + sometimes athletic team consulting. <a href="https://www.apta.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit;">APTA</a> 100,000+ members</div></div>
          <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">DPT doctorate required</div><div class="stat-label">Entry-level Doctor of Physical Therapy (DPT) required since 2016 per <a href="https://www.capteonline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit;">CAPTE</a> mandate. Pre-2016 MPT clinicians grandfathered. 3-year doctoral program + <a href="https://www.fsbpt.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit;">FSBPT NPTE</a> licensure exam</div></div>
          <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">Direct access since 2018</div><div class="stat-label">Florida direct access (no physician referral required) expanded 2018 supporting PT practice autonomy + private practice growth. Substantial scope expansion supporting practice ownership opportunity</div></div>
          <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">Chain consolidation pathway</div><div class="stat-label">Outpatient clinic chain consolidation (Select Medical, Athletico, US Physical Therapy, Ivy Rehab, ATI Physical Therapy) acquiring private practices at 5-8× EBITDA. Substantial wealth opportunity for senior practice owners</div></div>
        </div>
        <figure class="stats-bar-image"><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/4506222/pexels-photo-4506222.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1000" alt="Florida physical therapist DPT outpatient clinic" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/1000x750/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=PT+Practice';"></figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lede-section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="lede">Florida physical therapists operate at the intersection of doctoral-level training (DPT mandate since 2016), substantial private practice ownership opportunity, outpatient clinic chain consolidation, Florida retirement population orthopedic + geriatric + neurologic rehab demand, sports medicine subspecialty growth, and Florida no-state-income-tax favorable practice environment. <strong>Florida DPT practice spans five primary categories. Hospital-employed PT with W-2 base $75K-$95K + productivity bonuses + benefits + sometimes shift differentials (evenings + weekends + holidays). Common across FL hospital systems (HCA Florida, AdventHealth, BayCare, Memorial Healthcare, Cleveland Clinic Florida, Mayo Jacksonville, Tampa General, Jackson Health) inpatient + outpatient rehabilitation departments + ICU + cardiac rehab + acute care. Outpatient clinic chain PT at large chain operations (Select Medical + Athletico + US Physical Therapy + Ivy Rehab + ATI Physical Therapy + Pivot Physical Therapy + others) with W-2 base $70K-$95K + productivity bonus (typically tied to patient visits per week + collections + sometimes net revenue) + sometimes shift differential, total $80K-$115K. Chain model substantial PE-backed consolidation 2015-2026. Private practice PT owner operating S-corp election PLLC with W-2 wages from practice + S-corp K-1 distribution + sometimes multi-clinic ownership across 2-5 clinic locations + sometimes athletic team consulting + sometimes practice building real estate ownership. Senior single-clinic owners $150K-$250K+ income; multi-clinic owners $250K-$400K+ income. Practice ownership transitions from W-2 employment to S-corp ownership over 5-10 year mid-career arc. Home health / SNF (Skilled Nursing Facility) PT working PRN per-diem 1099 or W-2 with higher hourly rates ($55-$95/hour typical) + travel reimbursement + substantial scheduling flexibility. Common late-career PT transition supporting work-life balance + supplementing primary practice income + sometimes covering multiple sites. Total $85K-$130K+ depending on hours + setting mix. Sports medicine + pediatric + specialized PT with subspecialty fellowship + ABPTS board certification (OCS Orthopedic + SCS Sports + NCS Neurologic + GCS Geriatric + PCS Pediatric + CCS Cardiovascular) + sometimes athletic team consulting (high school + collegiate + professional teams) + sometimes private practice ownership + sometimes pediatric specialty clinic. Income $90K-$180K+ range</strong>. For mortgage qualifying, multi-source DPT income synthesizes under B3-3.1-01 for W-2 + productivity with 24-month averaging, B3-3.2-01 for 1099 PRN home health + athletic consulting, and B3-3.4-02 for practice owner S-corp K-1 + multi-clinic ownership with Form 1084 entity-level analysis. Professional / healthcare loan Non-QM with relaxed DTI + IBR/IDR available. <strong>Stairway Mortgage routinely handles Florida PT mortgages with multi-source synthesis + private practice K-1 + PRN 1099 + IBR/IDR + healthcare industry context.</strong> Skip to: <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/jumbo-loan/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline;">Jumbo</a>, <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline;">every program</a>, <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline;">calculators</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align: center; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="eyebrow">01 &middot; Florida physical therapist mortgage qualifying at a glance</div>
        <h2>Key facts every Florida physical therapist should know about qualifying.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="key-facts-grid">
        <div class="key-fact-card"><div class="key-fact-num">Multi-source DPT income</div><p class="key-fact-body">DPT income $75K-$400K+ spanning W-2 base + productivity + S-corp K-1 + PRN 1099 + sometimes athletic consulting. Multi-source synthesis under B3-3.1-01 + B3-3.2-01 + B3-3.4-02 frameworks combining hospital + outpatient + private practice + home health components.</p></div>
        <div class="key-fact-card"><div class="key-fact-num">Private practice S-corp K-1</div><p class="key-fact-body">Private practice owner S-corp K-1 under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.4-02</a> with Form 1084 cash-flow analysis. Add-backs: depreciation + medical equipment + CME + ABPTS + APTA dues + business use + practice expenses.</p></div>
        <div class="key-fact-card"><div class="key-fact-num">ABPTS + APTA credentialing</div><p class="key-fact-body"><a href="https://www.apta.org/your-career/abpts" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ABPTS board certification</a> (OCS / SCS / NCS / GCS / PCS / CCS) documented. APTA membership + FL Board of Physical Therapy Practice license active. Continuity narrative covers credentialing.</p></div>
        <div class="key-fact-card"><div class="key-fact-num">Professional loan + IBR/IDR</div><p class="key-fact-body">Professional / healthcare loan Non-QM programs include DPTs. Relaxed DTI + IBR/IDR student loan under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-6-05/monthly-debt-obligations" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-6-05</a>. DPTs typically $80K-$200K student loan with substantial DTI improvement.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="professions-section section-tinted" id="pt-roles">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="eyebrow">02 &middot; Florida physical therapist practice roles</div>
        <h2>The five DPT practice roles in Florida.</h2>
        <p>Florida physical therapist practice spans five primary categories across hospital + outpatient chain + private practice + home health + subspecialty structures.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="professions-grid">
        <div class="profession-card"><div class="profession-num">01</div><h3 class="profession-title">Hospital-Employed PT</h3><p class="profession-tag">"Hospital-employed DPT with W-2 base $75K-$95K + productivity bonuses + benefits + sometimes shift differentials. Common across FL hospital systems (HCA Florida, AdventHealth, BayCare, Memorial, Cleveland Clinic FL, Mayo Jacksonville). Inpatient + outpatient rehab + ICU + cardiac rehab + acute care."</p><ul class="profession-points"><li>W-2 $75K-$95K base</li><li>Hospital + outpatient + ICU mix</li><li>Productivity + shift differentials</li><li>Early-mid career path</li></ul><span class="profession-link" style="opacity: 0.65;">See hospital PT qualifying</span></div>
        <div class="profession-card"><div class="profession-num">02</div><h3 class="profession-title">Outpatient Chain PT</h3><p class="profession-tag">"Outpatient clinic chain PT (Select Medical, Athletico, US Physical Therapy, Ivy Rehab, ATI Physical Therapy, Pivot). W-2 base $70K-$95K + productivity bonus (patient visits + collections + sometimes net revenue) + sometimes shift differential. Total $80K-$115K. PE-backed consolidation 2015-2026."</p><ul class="profession-points"><li>Chain W-2 employment</li><li>Productivity bonuses</li><li>$80K-$115K total</li><li>Chain consolidation pathway</li></ul><span class="profession-link" style="opacity: 0.65;">See chain PT qualifying</span></div>
        <div class="profession-card"><div class="profession-num">03</div><h3 class="profession-title">Private Practice Owner</h3><p class="profession-tag">"Private practice PT owner operating S-corp election PLLC. W-2 wages + K-1 distribution + sometimes multi-clinic ownership (2-5 locations) + sometimes athletic team consulting + sometimes practice building real estate. Senior single-clinic $150K-$250K+; multi-clinic $250K-$400K+."</p><ul class="profession-points"><li>S-corp PLLC ownership</li><li>W-2 + K-1 + sometimes multi-clinic</li><li>$150K-$400K+ senior</li><li>Mid-career transition</li></ul><span class="profession-link" style="opacity: 0.65;">See practice owner qualifying</span></div>
        <div class="profession-card"><div class="profession-num">04</div><h3 class="profession-title">Home Health / SNF PRN PT</h3><p class="profession-tag">"Home health / SNF (Skilled Nursing Facility) PT working PRN per-diem 1099 or W-2 with higher hourly rates ($55-$95/hour). Travel reimbursement + flexibility + sometimes covering multiple sites. Late-career transition + work-life balance + supplementing primary income. $85K-$130K+ depending on hours."</p><ul class="profession-points"><li>PRN per-diem 1099 / W-2</li><li>$55-$95/hour rates</li><li>$85K-$130K+ flexible</li><li>Late-career + supplementing</li></ul><span class="profession-link" style="opacity: 0.65;">See PRN PT qualifying</span></div>
        <div class="profession-card"><div class="profession-num">05</div><h3 class="profession-title">Sports + Subspecialty PT</h3><p class="profession-tag">"Sports medicine + pediatric + specialized PT with subspecialty fellowship + ABPTS board certification (OCS / SCS / NCS / GCS / PCS / CCS). Sometimes athletic team consulting (high school + collegiate + professional) + private practice + pediatric clinic. $90K-$180K+ income."</p><ul class="profession-points"><li>Subspecialty fellowship</li><li>ABPTS board certification</li><li>Athletic team consulting</li><li>$90K-$180K+ range</li></ul><span class="profession-link" style="opacity: 0.65;">See subspecialty PT qualifying</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="income-structure">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="section-header"><div class="eyebrow">03 &middot; DPT practice structure analysis</div><h2>How DPT practice structure affects mortgage qualifying.</h2><p>Florida physical therapists operate across five primary structures each with distinct income reporting + qualifying implications.</p></div>
      <h3>Hospital W-2 employment</h3>
      <p>Hospital-employed DPT as W-2 employee of hospital + health system. W-2 base + productivity bonuses + benefits + sometimes shift differentials (evenings + weekends + holidays + ICU premium). Common across FL hospital systems with inpatient + outpatient rehab + ICU + cardiac rehab + acute care service lines. Multi-source under B3-3.1-01 with 24-month averaging on variable productivity + shift differentials. Most common structure for early to mid-career DPTs.</p>
      <h3>Outpatient chain W-2 + productivity</h3>
      <p>Outpatient clinic chain PT (Select Medical, Athletico, US Physical Therapy, Ivy Rehab, ATI Physical Therapy, Pivot) as W-2 employee. Base salary + productivity bonus typically tied to patient visits per week (target 10-13 visits per day typical) + collections + sometimes net revenue per visit + sometimes clinic profitability share. Chain model substantial PE-backed consolidation 2015-2026 with platforms acquiring private practices + employing W-2 clinicians.</p>
      <h3>Private practice S-corp ownership</h3>
      <p>Private practice PT owner operating S-corp election PLLC. Practice owner draws W-2 wages from practice + S-corp K-1 distribution from practice profit. Multi-clinic owners operate multiple S-corp entities or single S-corp with multiple locations. Sometimes practice building real estate held in separate LLC. Multi-entity Form 1084 cash-flow analysis. Multi-source under B3-3.1-01 + B3-3.4-02. Substantial practice ownership economics.</p>
      <h3>PRN per-diem 1099 / W-2 mix</h3>
      <p>Home health / SNF / hospital-based PRN per-diem PT working through staffing agency 1099 or direct W-2 PRN employment. Schedule C / 1120-S for 1099; W-2 for direct PRN employment. Higher hourly rates compensating for no benefits + variable scheduling. Common late-career PT supplementing primary practice income + work-life balance. Hybrid W-2 (primary) + PRN 1099 (supplementary) common structure.</p>
      <h3>Subspecialty fellowship + athletic consulting</h3>
      <p>Sports medicine + pediatric + neurologic + geriatric subspecialty DPT with ABPTS board certification + sometimes fellowship training + athletic team consulting 1099 (high school + collegiate + professional teams) + sometimes private practice ownership + sometimes pediatric specialty clinic. Hybrid practice income (W-2 + 1099 consulting + S-corp K-1) synthesized through multi-framework approach. Sports medicine DPTs frequently maintain primary outpatient clinic chain or private practice employment while supplementing through athletic team consulting contracts (Miami Heat, Marlins, Dolphins, Magic, Lightning, Buccaneers, Jaguars, Panthers for professional teams; University of Miami, Florida State, University of Florida, UCF, USF, FAU, FIU for collegiate; numerous high school athletic department contracts) generating substantial supplementary 1099 income $30K-$95K+ annually depending on team relationships + tenure + reputation. Pediatric DPTs frequently operate specialty clinics focused on developmental disorders + cerebral palsy + autism spectrum + early intervention with often early intervention contracting through Florida Department of Health Children&rsquo;s Medical Services programs supporting supplementary 1099 + sometimes contracted service revenue. Neurologic DPTs frequently work hospital inpatient rehabilitation + stroke recovery + Parkinson&rsquo;s specialty programs supporting hospital-employed W-2 with NCS subspecialty positioning. Geriatric DPTs frequently work skilled nursing facilities + home health + outpatient geriatric specialty supporting PRN per-diem + hospital-employed mix. All subspecialty patterns adapted under appropriate multi-source qualifying framework.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="per-diem-section per-diem-section--bg" style="background-image: url('https://images.pexels.com/photos/4506222/pexels-photo-4506222.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1800');">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="max-width: 760px;"><div class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">04 &middot; Florida physical therapy market context</div><h2 style="color: var(--paper);">Six things every Florida physical therapist should understand about market context.</h2><p style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.78);">Florida PT market operates within DPT doctorate transition + direct access expansion + outpatient chain consolidation + Florida retirement orthopedic + geriatric demand + sports medicine subspecialty growth + Florida no-state-income-tax favorable environment.</p></div>
      <div class="dark-grid">
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">A</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">DPT doctorate mandate</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">Entry-level Doctor of Physical Therapy (DPT) required since 2016 per CAPTE mandate. Pre-2016 MPT (Master of Physical Therapy) clinicians grandfathered. 3-year doctoral program + FSBPT NPTE licensure exam. Substantial educational investment supporting practice positioning + practice authority advocacy.</p></div>
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">B</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">Direct access expansion</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">Florida direct access (no physician referral required for evaluation + initial treatment) expanded 2018 supporting PT practice autonomy. ~30-day initial treatment window without referral. Substantial scope expansion supporting private practice growth + patient access + practice ownership opportunity.</p></div>
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">C</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">Chain consolidation pathway</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">Outpatient clinic chain consolidation 2015-2026 with PE-backed platforms (Select Medical, Athletico, US Physical Therapy, Ivy Rehab, ATI Physical Therapy, Pivot) acquiring private practices at 5-8× EBITDA. Sale + earnout + equity rollover + post-acquisition employment pathway. Substantial wealth opportunity for senior practice owners.</p></div>
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">D</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">FL retirement orthopedic demand</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">Florida retirement population substantial PT demand: orthopedic rehab (joint replacement + spine + sports injury) + geriatric rehab (fall prevention + balance + functional mobility) + neurologic rehab (stroke + Parkinson&rsquo;s + MS) + cardiac rehab. Medicare patient concentration substantial. Driving substantial DPT demand across all categories.</p></div>
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">E</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">Sports medicine subspecialty growth</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">Sports medicine PT subspecialty substantial growth with athletic + recreational sports injury patient base. FL professional sports teams (Heat, Marlins, Dolphins, Magic, Lightning, Buccaneers, Jaguars, Panthers) + collegiate + high school athletic team consulting. Running + endurance sports market expansion. ABPTS SCS subspecialty certification supporting differentiation.</p></div>
        <div class="dark-card"><div class="dark-num">F</div><h3 class="dark-card-title" style="color: var(--paper);">FL no-state-income-tax</h3><p class="dark-card-body" style="color: rgba(250,250,247,0.72);">FL no state income tax substantial PT income preservation. Senior practice owner $250K-$400K+: California (13.3%) saves $33K-$53K+; New York (10.9%) saves $27K-$44K+ annually relocating to Florida. Multi-million lifetime tax preservation driving substantial DPT relocations 2020-2026.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="section-header"><div class="eyebrow">05 &middot; DPT W-2 + productivity B3-3.1-01 deep dive</div><h2>How Stairway handles DPT W-2 + productivity qualifying.</h2><p>Hospital + outpatient chain employed DPT W-2 base + productivity bonuses + shift differentials require B3-3.1-01 framework treatment.</p></div>
      <h3>Step 1 &mdash; W-2 + productivity documentation</h3>
      <p>2-year W-2s + 30-day paystubs + productivity documentation (patient visits per week reports + productivity bonus statements + shift differential payroll detail + sometimes net revenue per visit reports for chain employment). Hospital / health system / outpatient chain VOE + practice agreement documenting compensation structure. Productivity bonuses typically 10-25% of total compensation for outpatient chain DPTs.</p>
      <h3>Step 2 &mdash; 24-month averaging on productivity + shift differentials</h3>
      <p>Productivity bonuses + shift differentials treated as variable income under B3-3.1-01 with 24-month averaging. Documentation through productivity reports + bonus statements + W-2 reconciliation. Senior DPTs with stable productivity show predictable baseline. Junior DPTs + new positions may show productivity ramp requiring narrative explanation.</p>
      <h3>Step 3 &mdash; ABPTS + APTA + DPT narrative</h3>
      <p>Continuity narrative documents: APTA membership, ABPTS board certification if applicable (OCS / SCS / NCS / GCS / PCS / CCS) + recertification status, FL Board of Physical Therapy Practice license active + clean disciplinary, CAPTE-accredited DPT program completion or pre-2016 MPT grandfathered, hospital privileges + practice tenure, fellowship subspecialty certification if applicable.</p>
      <h3>Step 4 &mdash; Hybrid W-2 + PRN supplementary</h3>
      <p>DPTs frequently maintain primary W-2 employment + supplementary PRN per-diem income (home health + SNF + hospital-based PRN). Documentation through staffing agency contracts + 1099-MISC statements + direct PRN employment paystubs. Hybrid income supplements core W-2 + supports continuity narrative. Common late-career structure for work-life balance.</p>
      <h3>Step 5 &mdash; Professional / healthcare loan eligibility</h3>
      <p>Professional / healthcare loan Non-QM programs increasingly available for DPTs (similar to physician loan but expanded to allied health professionals). Programs offer: relaxed DTI to 45-50%, IBR-based student loan treatment, low down payment 3-10%, up to $1M-$1.5M loan amounts, no PMI requirement. Common path for early-career + mid-career DPTs purchasing primary residence.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="section-header"><div class="eyebrow">06 &middot; Practice ownership + multi-clinic B3-3.4-02 deep dive</div><h2>How Stairway handles DPT practice ownership + multi-clinic qualifying.</h2><p>Senior DPTs operating as private practice owners + multi-clinic owners require multi-entity B3-3.4-02 framework treatment.</p></div>
      <h3>Step 1 &mdash; 2-year personal + practice entity returns</h3>
      <p>2-year personal tax returns (Form 1040 + Schedule E for K-1s + W-2 from practice) + 2-year practice entity returns (Form 1120-S for S-corp / Form 1065 for partnership) + 2-year multi-clinic entity returns if applicable + 2-year practice building real estate entity returns if applicable. Schedule K-1 documenting DPT share of practice profit + multi-clinic profit + RE profit + distribution amounts.</p>
      <h3>Step 2 &mdash; Practice + multi-clinic ownership documentation</h3>
      <p>Practice S-corp shareholder agreement or partnership agreement documenting DPT ownership %. Multi-clinic ownership documentation for each clinic location entity. Practice building real estate holding entity operating agreement if applicable. Capital account balances at each entity documented through K-1 + entity balance sheets.</p>
      <h3>Step 3 &mdash; Form 1084 multi-entity cash-flow</h3>
      <p>Form 1084 cash-flow analysis applied at each operating entity (primary practice + multi-clinic locations + sometimes RE) adding back: depreciation (substantial for practice with rehabilitation equipment + medical equipment + sometimes office space + clinic build-out), medical equipment financing interest, business use of vehicle, CME + ABPTS recertification + subspecialty board, malpractice insurance + tail coverage, professional dues (APTA, state society, ABPTS), business use of home if applicable.</p>
      <h3>Step 4 &mdash; W-2 + multi-entity K-1 synthesis</h3>
      <p>Practice owner receives: W-2 wages from practice (reasonable compensation per IRS standards) + S-corp K-1 from practice + sometimes K-1 from additional clinic entities + sometimes K-1 from practice building real estate. W-2 under B3-3.1-01. Multi-entity K-1 under B3-3.4-02 with Form 1084 at each entity. Multi-source synthesis combining all components produces comprehensive picture.</p>
      <h3>Step 5 &mdash; Chain acquisition + practice transition pathway</h3>
      <p>Chain acquisition (Select Medical + Athletico + US Physical Therapy + Ivy Rehab + ATI Physical Therapy) common pathway for senior practice owners. Sale + earnout + equity rollover + post-acquisition employment pathway. Acquisition multiples 5-8× EBITDA typical. Multi-source post-acquisition: W-2 + equity rollover units + earnout. Stairway routinely handles post-acquisition refinance + cash-out + new purchase coordination for DPTs in practice transition.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="section-header"><div class="eyebrow">07 &middot; Multi-source synthesis for DPTs</div><h2>How Stairway combines W-2 + productivity + K-1 + PRN 1099 + spouse income into qualifying.</h2><p>DPTs with multi-source income synthesize each component under appropriate framework.</p></div>
      <h3>Step 1 &mdash; W-2 + productivity primary anchor</h3>
      <p>W-2 base + productivity bonuses + shift differentials synthesized under B3-3.1-01 with 24-month averaging on variable components. Primary anchor for hospital + outpatient chain employed DPT multi-source income.</p>
      <h3>Step 2 &mdash; Practice + multi-clinic K-1 distribution</h3>
      <p>Practice S-corp K-1 + multi-clinic K-1 + sometimes practice building real estate K-1 synthesized under B3-3.4-02 with multi-entity Form 1084 analysis. Add-backs comprehensive at each operating entity.</p>
      <h3>Step 3 &mdash; PRN 1099 + athletic consulting</h3>
      <p>PRN per-diem 1099 home health / SNF income + athletic team consulting 1099 (if applicable) synthesized under B3-3.2-01 with Schedule C / 1120-S + Form 1084 add-backs (CME + APTA + ABPTS + business use + travel). Common late-career DPT supplementary income structure.</p>
      <h3>Step 4 &mdash; IBR/IDR student loan treatment</h3>
      <p>Student loan IBR/IDR payment under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-6-05/monthly-debt-obligations" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-6-05</a> + professional loan treatment. DPTs typically carry $80K-$200K student loan debt with IBR/PAYE/REPAYE income-driven repayment substantial DTI improvement. SAVE plan replacing REPAYE provides even lower IBR payment calculation starting 2024-2025 cycle.</p>
      <h3>Step 5 &mdash; Spouse W-2 + final DTI</h3>
      <p>Spouse W-2 income (if applicable) added to multi-source synthesis. Combined monthly qualifying income calculated. Federal tax + Social Security + Medicare deductions applied (FL no state income tax substantial advantage). Net qualifying flows to DTI calculation. Common DPT + spouse profiles: spouse healthcare professional + spouse non-healthcare W-2 professional.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

